                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d875">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 (Potsdam)/7–3145</note>
                <head>No. 875<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Proposal by the British Delegation</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1945-07-23">Undated</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">U. K. Proposal</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Article</hi> 19 <hi rend="smallcaps">of “Economic
                        Principles”</hi>
                </p>
                <p>19. After payment of Reparations enough resources must be left to enable the
                    German people to subsist without external assistance. In working out the
                    economic balance of Germany the necessary means <pb facs="1006" n="812"
                        xml:id="pg_812"/> must be provided to pay for imports approved by the
                    Governments concerned.<note n="1" xml:id="d875fn1">Another version of this
                        paper, with the same heading, found in the <persName corresp="#p_PEW1"
                            >Pauley</persName> Files, ends this sentence with the words “approved by
                        the Control Council”.</note> The proceeds of the exports from current
                    production and stocks shall be available in the first place for payment for such
                    imports.</p>
            </div>
